@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}

 CLIExchange is a CLI replacement for the standard @{b}Commodore@{ub} tool @{i}Exchange@{ui}.
 The later is based on a (very basic) graphical interface and awfully lacks
 a command line access to control the Commodities. Also, it's unable to send
 a given message to all running commodities with a simple key stroke.

 CLIExchange fills these needs and besides is much smaller:

        Exchange 37.4   /WB2.0      12460 bytes (very lousy interface)
        Exchange 38.9   /WB2.1       6780 bytes
        Exchange 40.1   /WB3.1       6748 bytes

     CLIExchange  1.4                 584 bytes

 CLIExchange has been designed to be called from the CLI, a shell script,
 a @{i}ToolManager@{ui} menu, dock or hotkey, @{i}BrowserII@{ui} or whatever similar tool you
 may be using.
@endnode

