@node Requirements "Requirements"
@{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

 CLIExchange runs under at least release 2.02 of the system since it uses
 dos.library V36+ command line parsing. Obviously, the commodities.library
 must also be present in your LIBS: assignment.
@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"
@{b}USAGE@{ub}

 CLIExchange <list of commodities> <command>

 The first argument is a list of commodity names. Be aware that these names
 are case sensitive and must be quoted if containing spaces. However, a list
 of commodity names isn't mandatory and if none has been specified, then ALL
 currently running commodities will receive the given command.

 <command> is an optional argument defining the kind of message CLIExchange
 should sent to the commodities. It can take one of the following values:

    DISABLE  : Disables the commodity
    ENABLE   : Enables the commodity
    APPEAR   : Pops-up the commodity interface
    DISAPPEAR: Hides the commodity interface
    KILL     : Quits the commodity
    UNIQUE   : Notifies the commodity that it has been re-launched.
               Most commodities react to command by showing their interface.

 Note that some commands aren't supported by all commodities and are in that
 case simply ignored.

    INFO     : Displays the commodity title and description
@endnode

@node Examples "Examples"
@{b}EXAMPLES@{ub}

  > CLIExchange @{i}KILL@{ui} "Magic Menu" GrabIFF Yak "Arq 1.78"

    will quit the four commodities above.


  > CLIExchange @{i}DISABLE@{ui}

    will disable all running commodities because no list has been provided.


  > CLIExchange ToolManager PowerCache INFO

    will display the above commodities title and description


  > CLIExchange

    will display a list of all commodities.
@endnode

